-- ArcelorMittal Invests $8 Million in Romania to Reduce Pollution
-- B y   I r i n a   S a v u
-- 2012-07-19T09:51:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-19/arcelormittal-invests-8-million-in-romania-to-reduce-pollution.html
ArcelorMittal (MT)  Galati SA, the
Romanian unit of the world’s largest steelmaker ArcelorMittal,
invested 6.6 million euros ($8 million) over the past year to
reduce pollution.  The Romanian producer has invested more than $168 million
in the past decade in environment protection projects, the
company said in an e-mailed statement today.  “We are committed to taking all necessary measures to
ensure full compliance with European Union requirements and
local legislation,” ArcelorMittal Galati Chief Executive
Officer Bruno Ribo said in the statement. “We have implemented
a rigorous environment protection program that we continued
despite the economic crisis.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Irina Savu in Bucharest at 
 isavu@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  